</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556EDDD38B9FF78F8BDFBE5FC72" pageId="652" pageNumber="653" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEDDD38B9FF78F8BDFAFEFDFC" blockId="652.[136,778,1669,2070]" lastBlockId="652.[810,1452,173,948]" pageId="652" pageNumber="653">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDDD38B9FF78F8BDFE07F84C" bold="true" box="[189,450,1907,1933]" pageId="652" pageNumber="653">Descriptionoffemale</emphasis>
. Body (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDDD38B9FDE6F8BAFD5EF84F" box="[547,667,1908,1934]" captionStart="FIGURE 443" captionStartId="653.[136,240,1263,1287]" captionTargetBox="[182,1414,221,1185]" captionTargetId="figure-18@653.[136,1451,194,1211]" captionTargetPageId="653" captionText="FIGURE 443. Socotradelphys unipedata gen. et sp. nov., female.A, habitus, dorsal; B, cephalic region, ventral; C, urosome; D, antenna. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592206" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592206/files/figure.png" pageId="652" pageNumber="653">Fig. 443A</figureCitation>
) maggotshaped, graduallybroadeningposteriorly, consistingof unsegmented prosome and small, rudimentary urosome, with thin, soft epidermis. Bodylength 2.12 mm; body width 0.65 mm across widest region in posterior 20% of body. Body surface ornamented with sparsely scattered, fine spinules. Cephalosome (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDDD38B9FB43FF01FAC4FF28" box="[1158,1281,207,233]" captionStart="FIGURE 443" captionStartId="653.[136,240,1263,1287]" captionTargetBox="[182,1414,221,1185]" captionTargetId="figure-18@653.[136,1451,194,1211]" captionTargetPageId="653" captionText="FIGURE 443. Socotradelphys unipedata gen. et sp. nov., female.A, habitus, dorsal; B, cephalic region, ventral; C, urosome; D, antenna. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592206" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592206/files/figure.png" pageId="652" pageNumber="653">Fig. 443B</figureCitation>
) with pair of swollen, lateral processes; processes bulbous, gradually broadening distally, directed ventro-medially, extending to level of tip of labrum. Urosome (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDDD38B9FB6AFEFBFAE5FE8E" box="[1199,1312,309,335]" captionStart="FIGURE 443" captionStartId="653.[136,240,1263,1287]" captionTargetBox="[182,1414,221,1185]" captionTargetId="figure-18@653.[136,1451,194,1211]" captionTargetPageId="653" captionText="FIGURE 443. Socotradelphys unipedata gen. et sp. nov., female.A, habitus, dorsal; B, cephalic region, ventral; C, urosome; D, antenna. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592206" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592206/files/figure.png" pageId="652" pageNumber="653">Fig. 443C</figureCitation>
) indistinctly 2-segmented, positionedondorsal surfaceof prosome near posterior end; first somite obscure, fused with prosome; second wider than long (77×94 μm), bilobed posteriorly, with deep posteromedian incision in rear margin; ornamented with scattered spinules. Caudal rami small, lobate, 19×14 μm, indistinctly articulated from abdomen, unarmed but ornamented with several spinules.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEDDD38B9FC9AFD88FB0BFC50" blockId="652.[810,1452,173,948]" pageId="652" pageNumber="653">
Rostrum and antennules absent. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDDD38B9FAF4FD8BFA66FD9E" box="[1329,1443,581,607]" captionStart="FIGURE 443" captionStartId="653.[136,240,1263,1287]" captionTargetBox="[182,1414,221,1185]" captionTargetId="figure-18@653.[136,1451,194,1211]" captionTargetPageId="653" captionText="FIGURE 443. Socotradelphys unipedata gen. et sp. nov., female.A, habitus, dorsal; B, cephalic region, ventral; C, urosome; D, antenna. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592206" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592206/files/figure.png" pageId="652" pageNumber="653">Fig. 443D</figureCitation>
) extremely small, 2-segmented, positioned between base of labrum and ventrolateral lateral processes (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDDD38B9FAECFD47FA5AFD62" box="[1321,1439,649,675]" captionStart="FIGURE 443" captionStartId="653.[136,240,1263,1287]" captionTargetBox="[182,1414,221,1185]" captionTargetId="figure-18@653.[136,1451,194,1211]" captionTargetPageId="653" captionText="FIGURE 443. Socotradelphys unipedata gen. et sp. nov., female.A, habitus, dorsal; B, cephalic region, ventral; C, urosome; D, antenna. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592206" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592206/files/figure.png" pageId="652" pageNumber="653">Fig. 443B</figureCitation>
); secondsegment subdivided by lateral constriction, tipped withsmall claw. Labrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDDD38B9FB9FFD03FB15FD26" box="[1114,1232,717,743]" captionStart="FIGURE 443" captionStartId="653.[136,240,1263,1287]" captionTargetBox="[182,1414,221,1185]" captionTargetId="figure-18@653.[136,1451,194,1211]" captionTargetPageId="653" captionText="FIGURE 443. Socotradelphys unipedata gen. et sp. nov., female.A, habitus, dorsal; B, cephalic region, ventral; C, urosome; D, antenna. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592206" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592206/files/figure.png" pageId="652" pageNumber="653">Fig. 443B</figureCitation>
) large, longerthan wide, tapering towards rounded apex. Mouth visible beneath labrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDDD38B9FC2AFCDFFBACFCEA" box="[1007,1129,785,811]" captionStart="FIGURE 443" captionStartId="653.[136,240,1263,1287]" captionTargetBox="[182,1414,221,1185]" captionTargetId="figure-18@653.[136,1451,194,1211]" captionTargetPageId="653" captionText="FIGURE 443. Socotradelphys unipedata gen. et sp. nov., female.A, habitus, dorsal; B, cephalic region, ventral; C, urosome; D, antenna. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592206" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592206/files/figure.png" pageId="652" pageNumber="653">Fig. 443B</figureCitation>
). Mouthparts absent. Leg 1 represented by paired globular lobes positioned close to each other on mid-ventral surface, posterior to apex of labrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDDD38B9FC4DFCB9FC3BFC50" box="[904,1022,887,913]" captionStart="FIGURE 443" captionStartId="653.[136,240,1263,1287]" captionTargetBox="[182,1414,221,1185]" captionTargetId="figure-18@653.[136,1451,194,1211]" captionTargetPageId="653" captionText="FIGURE 443. Socotradelphys unipedata gen. et sp. nov., female.A, habitus, dorsal; B, cephalic region, ventral; C, urosome; D, antenna. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592206" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592206/files/figure.png" pageId="652" pageNumber="653">Fig. 443B</figureCitation>
). Legs 2–5 absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEDDD38B9FC9AFC57FBE5FC72" blockId="652.[810,1452,173,948]" box="[863,1056,921,948]" pageId="652" pageNumber="653">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDDD38B9FC9AFC57FC59FC72" bold="true" box="[863,924,921,947]" pageId="652" pageNumber="653">Male</emphasis>
